
[1]enticement

   ENTI'CEMENT, n. The act or practice of inciting to evil; instigation;
   as the enticements of evil companions.

   1. Means of inciting to evil; that which seduces by exciting the
   passions. Flattery often operates as an enticement to sin.

   2. Allurement.
